<div id="tab-isometric" class="tab-content">
  <div class="section-eyebrow">Clinical Application</div>
  <div class="section-title">Isometric Applications: PIMA vs HIMA</div>

  <div class="card-2col">
    <div class="iso-card">
      <div class="iso-card-badge hima">Yielding / Resisting</div>
      <div class="iso-card-title">HIMA — Hold Isometric</div>
      <p>Resisting an external force that is trying to move you</p>
      <div class="iso-visual">🧍 ⬅️<br><span style="font-size:0.72rem;color:var(--muted);">"Hold against the force"</span></div>
      <div class="iso-inner">
        <div class="iso-inner-title">Characteristics</div>
        <ul>
          <li>Longer time under tension</li>
          <li>Lower peak forces</li>
          <li>Greater endurance focus</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="iso-inner">
        <div class="iso-inner-title">Cue Strategy</div>
        <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:var(--gold);font-style:italic;">"Gently resist" / "Hold steady"</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="iso-card">
      <div class="iso-card-badge pima">Overcoming / Pushing</div>
      <div class="iso-card-title">PIMA — Push Isometric</div>
      <p>Pushing against an immovable object with maximal intent</p>
      <div class="iso-visual">🧍 ➡️<br><span style="font-size:0.72rem;color:var(--muted);">"Push against immovable"</span></div>
      <div class="iso-inner">
        <div class="iso-inner-title">Characteristics</div>
        <ul>
          <li>Higher peak forces possible</li>
          <li>Variable intent (gradual → ballistic)</li>
          <li>Greater strength / power focus</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="iso-inner">
        <div class="iso-inner-title">Cue Strategy</div>
        <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:var(--gold);font-style:italic;">"Gradually crush" / "Explode against"</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="callout callout-gold">
    <div class="callout-title">Clinical Implication</div>
    <p>HIMA suits early-stage rehab where tissue tolerance is limited — longer TUT, lower peak forces. PIMA allows progressive cueing from gradual to ballistic intent, enabling strength and power development within the same exercise.</p>
  </div>
</div>

